news.title: Bengaluru metro gears up for extension of green line
news.para: Bengaluru Metro Rail Corporation Limited (BMRCL) is gearing up for the much-awaited launch of the 3.7 km Nagasandra to Madavara metro stretch on the Green Line.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance raises Rs 835 crore through social loan
news.para: The loan has a three-year maturity, and it is benchmarked to the three-month secured overnight financing rate (SOFR) plus 200 basis points. The prevailing SOFR is 5.3%.

news.title: UltraTech Cement acquires additional 25% stake in UAE-based RAKWCT
news.para: The acquisition was made by UltraTech Cement Middle East Investments Ltd (UCMEIL), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Indian cement maker in the UAE.

news.title: No project can fail if builders maintain financial discipline: Haryana RERA member
news.para: "There is a need of rationalisation of interest rates, lending rates, because once the lending rates are reduced, certainly the investors or the homebuyers come forward. And builders are also happy to deliver at least possible costs," Arora said.

news.title: China’s finance ministry dials up scrutiny for audit firms after Evergrande probe: Sources
news.para: The tighter scrutiny, which has not been previously reported, is mainly focused on Deloitte, EY, PwC, KPMG and their audits of some financial firms as well as highly leveraged companies, said the people.

news.title: Steel prices in China hit three-month low on poor construction demand
news.para: Latest data from China showed domestic demand continued to recover at a slow pace, and construction data showed double digit percentage fall in the first five months of the year.

news.title: UK’s Barratt expects 7% drop in homebuilding targets for FY25
news.para: The housing sector is betting on a dynamic shift in homebuilding policy under the new Labour government, mainly to tackle planning-related issues, as a delay in interest rate cuts has tempered hopes for a fast-paced recovery.

news.title: Germany: Vonovia's CEO sees surge in real estate bankruptcies
news.para: The bleak assessment from Rolf Buch, the CEO of Vonovia and one of the nation's property titans, defies hopes for an imminent turnaround as the sector goes through its worst crisis in a generation.

news.title: Britain's Vistry expects 7% jump in profit in H1 2024
news.para: The sector will be encouraged by the new Labour government's pledge to overhaul planning rules as part of efforts to build 1.5 million new homes over the next five years.

news.title: Mumbai: EOW arrests Kamal Mills' owner in fraud case
news.para: Subsequently, a case was registered against Govani under sections 409 (criminal breach of trust), 420 (Cheating and dishonestly inducing delivery of property), and 34 of the Indian Penal Code.

news.title: Odisha government asks district administrations to identify land sharks, evict them
news.para: "The govt land is meant for public use and for development projects. Squatters have been creating problems. They need to be removed at the soonest possible," Majhi was quoted as saying in a statement issued by his office.

news.title: Sand prices skyrocket in Rajasthan due to excavation ban, expired leases
news.para: According to the ministry of environment and forests (MoEF) guidelines, leaseholders can’t excavate sand from the river. Traders are selling sand from stockpiles collected before the rain.

news.title: New defence ministry clause irks cantonment residents in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: As per the new clause  added recently by the Union ministry of defence into the modalities of transferring assets from cantonment boards to state municipal bodies the Army will continue to be the owner of all the land on which private houses have been built.

news.title: Gurugram development body's board to present Rs 2,887 crore budget for FY25
news.para: The Authority’s board will present its Rs 2,887 crore budget for FY 2024-25, apart from projects worth Rs 3,500 to chief minister Nayab Singh Saini for approval as he chairs the meeting in Chandigarh.

news.title: Chhattisgarh government to provide houses to over 47,000 families
news.para: The socio-economic survey conducted by the state government from April 1 to April 30 last year covering 59.79 lakh families identified 47,090 families as homeless.

news.title: Alphacorp to invest Rs 350 crore in residential project in Gurugram
news.para: The company will develop 500,000 sq ft on two 2 land parcels - one 2.38 acre and another 2.36 acre, There will be 29-floors and the company will develop 200 units, expecting a revenue of Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Global BFSI companies take up commercial spaces in Hyderabad
news.para: TOI has learnt that one of the biggest transactions in office space in H1 2024 has been done by Cigna Healthcare at around 9 lakh sq ft, followed by Metlife at around 2.5 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Tata Realty plans to triple its office space portfolio in seven years
news.para: Since most of its current portfolio is part of Special Economic Zones (SEZs), TRIL is applying for their denotification in line with recent government rules.

news.title: Noida authority seeks action against builders for extracting water
news.para: In the letter, Authority CEO Lokesh M noted that they have been receiving frequent complaints from the public about various developers engaging in illegal dewatering during construction work, especially in sectors 153, 154, and 156.
